feat(canary): wire synthetic checkup through main crawl pipeline with typed UI contract

Introduce the canary module (dashboard state, TypedDict JSON contract aligned with
the canary UI, quadrant probe scaffolding, and CanaryCrawlStrategy) so checkups
reuse Crawlee, anti-bot, and MasterDispatcher instead of a parallel path.

refactor(site): decouple audit workspace and narrow assembled pipeline types

Add AuditWorkspaceProvider (Protocol) and a frozen SitePipeline dataclass capturing
the post-assembly handler graph as non-optional components; replace direct
SiteAuditCenter coupling where a workspace abstraction suffices. Extract
_resolve_seed_urls so canary strategies can supply fixed seed URLs without
duplicating the main run loop.

fix(crawlee): reconcile factory with current Crawlee storage and typing expectations

Return type[BrowserFactory] from the lazy factory accessor; inject
MemoryStorageClient for is_canary tasks to isolate ephemeral queues/stores from
default on-disk storage; assert fingerprint profile presence before pre-navigation
hooks; type proxy URL lists as list[str | None] for ProxyConfiguration invariance.

refactor(bridge): tighten UI bridge typing and remove brittle suppressions

Return CanaryDashboardDict from fetch_canary_dashboard; delegate payload assembly to
the canary dashboard builder with dispatcher_running / is_canary_active semantics;
replace bare os.startfile type: ignore with a guarded callable check; add explicit
null checks for webview.create_window and window.events; replace silent except
pass blocks with structured debug logging where appropriate; implement
run_canary_checkup by submitting an is_canary task via asyncio.run_coroutine_threadsafe.

feat(app): expose canary run visibility on the dispatcher

Add task_info.is_canary on settings and is_canary_run_active on MasterDispatcher
for dashboard locking semantics while a canary strategy is active.

chore(types): add Pyright configuration and local stub typings

Add pyrightconfig.json and typings/ shims to close third-party annotation gaps
supporting the above refactors.
